{{Top|leg}}
The '''Flimmel tree''' was a species of carnivorous mushroom native to [[Xagobah/Legends|Xagobah]]. Running vertically down the tree's stalk below its umbrella-shaped pileus was a mouth filled with row upon row of razor-sharp crimson teeth and a pale tongue. When unsuspecting prey wandered near a Flimmel tree during its feeding hours, the tree would extend large slimy folds of fungus outwards like huge [[Mynock/Legends|mynock]] wings. These folds would cover prey in sticky webs until they were wrapped up in a slime cocoon. As the slime suffocated the prey, the folds would slowly retract and pull them towards the tree's gapping maw. The trees were part of a large colony that shared a common root system, with the entire plant living many millennia. If one tree was hurt, the entire organism would be impacted.<ref name="Boba Fett: A New Threat">''[[Boba Fett: A New Threat]]''</ref>

[[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] was almost consumed by a Flimmel tree when he came to Xagobah in search of [[Wat Tambor/Legends|Wat Tambor]]. He managed to escape by stunning the fungus with a [[Spray stick/Legends|Stokhli spray stick]].

